    <date day="04" month="July" year="2012"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>Sunsetting IPv4 refers to the process of turning off IPv4
   definitively.  It can be seen as the final phase of the migration to
   IPv6.  This memo analyses difficulties arising when sunsetting IPv4,
   and identifies the gaps resulting in additional work.</t>
    </abstract>
